This paper discusses a probabilistic framework for tracking uncertainties in robotic manipulation, which is a core topic in robotics (cs.RO). The framework involves perception and physical interaction, which are related to computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses different representations of uncertainties, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and control systems (cs.SY).
